(1) Except as otherwise provided under this Act the functions of the Conference shall be to exercise the corporate powers of a self-management enterprise .
Except as otherwise provided under this Act the functions of the Conference shall be to exercise the corporate powers of a self-management enterprise .
(2) Without prejudice to subsection (1), the Conference shall— (a) formulate policies for the smooth operations of a self-management enterprise ; (b) consider and where appropriate, approve the development plans of a self-management enterprise ; (c) consider and approve the investment plans of a self-management enterprise ; (d) elect members of the Board ; and (e) give directives to and exercise control over the Board .
